---
const terminalLines = [
  '$ kubectl get nodes -o wide',
  '$ terraform plan -out=platform.tfplan',
  '$ helm upgrade --install platform ./charts',
  '$ argocd app sync production',
  '$ kubectl top pods -n platform',
  '$ terraform apply -auto-approve',
];
---

<section class="about section" id="about">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section-title reveal">Building Platforms at Scale</h2>
    <p class="section-subtitle reveal">// where infrastructure meets impact</p>

    <div class="about-grid">
      <div class="about-prose reveal">
        <p>
          I build the platforms that engineering teams ship on. At Abridge AI, I helped grow the
          platform engineering organization from 1 to 25, standing up the cloud infrastructure,
          Kubernetes clusters, and CI/CD pipelines that let a healthcare AI company move fast
          without breaking compliance.
        </p>
        <p>
          Over 12+ years, I've focused on the intersection of developer experience and production
          reliability&mdash;designing systems where "it just works" is the result of a lot of
          deliberate engineering underneath. Cloud-native architectures, infrastructure as code,
          and a philosophy that the best platform is the one developers don't have to think about.
        </p>
        <p>
          What sets me apart is the breadth behind the depth. The hobby-tech&mdash;game engines,
          ML pipelines, systems programming&mdash;isn't a distraction. It's the reason I can
          debug a kernel panic, reason about GPU memory, or intuit why a distributed system is
          misbehaving. Curiosity is the cheat code.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="about-terminal reveal">
        <div class="terminal">
          <div class="terminal-bar">
            <span class="terminal-dot" style="background: #ef4444;"></span>
            <span class="terminal-dot" style="background: var(--accent-amber);"></span>
            <span class="terminal-dot" style="background: #22c55e;"></span>
            <span class="terminal-title mono">platform@grym:~</span>
          </div>
          <div class="terminal-body mono">
            {terminalLines.map((line, i) => (
              <div class="terminal-line" style={`animation-delay: ${i * 3}s;`}>
                <span class="terminal-prompt">â–¶</span>
                <span class="terminal-text">{line}</span>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .about-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .about-prose p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .about-prose p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Terminal */
  .terminal {
    background: rgba(10, 14, 23, 0.9);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow: hidden;
    position: sticky;
    top: 6rem;
  }

  .terminal-bar {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.8);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }

  .terminal-dot {
    width: 12px;
    height: 12px;
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  .terminal-title {
    margin-left: auto;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .terminal-body {
    padding: 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    line-height: 2;
    min-height: 280px;
  }

  .terminal-line {
    opacity: 0;
    animation: terminalType 3s ease forwards;
    animation-iteration-count: 1;
  }

  .terminal-prompt {
    color: var(--accent-amber);
    margin-right: 0.5rem;
  }

  .terminal-text {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  @keyframes terminalType {
    0% { opacity: 0; transform: translateX(-4px); }
    10% { opacity: 1; transform: translateX(0); }
    100% { opacity: 1; transform: translateX(0); }
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .terminal {
      position: static;
    }
  }
</style>
